Operational Goal:
Connecting Routes to / from KUAC
To force traffic via dedicated routes/points allowing transition to  upper airspace (sector above FL315) and ensure LoA and OLDI conditions.
Route options 1-b are available for (slow climbing) long range flights as listed via a dedicated RAD ANNEX 3B DCT GAPTO -KOGOL (FL225-FL660). For ATC the dedicated route triggers an expected vertical profile above FL315 only after KOGOL (finetuned by PTR) and ensures correct OLDI exchange.
Route option c can only be filed, if not to listed destinations (the vertical trajectory is expected at FL315 -division FL between Munich ACC and KUAC- before KOGOL) After TULSI either ATS routes or FRA can be used.
Option d can be used for all destinations, but is only available for departures being above FL315 at TUNUM.

        ii) FLT-TYPE (M)_x000D_

    e. XNG LSASFRA - LFEECTAE BDRY
Operational Goal:
To create structural limitations to segregate climbing and descending traffic from overflights.
a. GILIR DCT NINTU a direct option for overflights.
b. GILIR DCT TUROM (and then MILPA) is only available for Basel group departures and provides lateral spacing from overflights to facilitate climb.
c. GILIR DCT GEVEA to segregate overflights from the climbing/descending traffic via TUROM and MILPA.
d. GILIR DCT MILPA is only available for traffic arriving LFLU/MH to provide lateral spacing for the descent and to provide a connection for State flights that must avoid Swiss territory.
5. To allow for GILIR to be used as an exit point
Remarks: LSASFRA

Utilization:
NOT AVBL FOR TFC
ARR/DEP BKPR
Operational Goal:
To force flight planning avoid the airspace of Republic of Serbia.
Use of ICAO designator BKPR is not allowed for traffic intending to use airspace of the Republic of Serbia. Usage of Republic of Serbia airspace for traffic ARR/DEP LYPR is not allowed except for NATO/KFOR/EUFOR military flights or flights with properly obtained diplomatic clearances (see Serbia / Montenegro AIP SUP 3/13 and NATO SPINS - Regulations for aircraft operating as GAT in the Balkans).
To avoid FPL REJ recommended route options in SECSI FRA are NILKU DCT AKIKA for ARR BKPR and RETRA DCT GACMO for DEP BKPR. In fixed route network environment (below FL205) traffic with ARR/DEP BKPR should use options OSLUD M867 MODRA N142 AKIKA or KEB/GILUK DCT NILKU N132 AKIKA for arrivals and option RETRA L604 GACMO for departures.
Remarks: SECSI FRA

Operational Goal:
1. All flight plans from London ACC entering Maastricht UAC via KONAN shall route via KOK thereafter.
2. To avoid sharp turns into specific sectors of Reims/Paris ACCs, into DECO sectors of Maastricht UAC or specified points. Traffic shall file via or south of line KOK-REMBA.
3. Traffic via Ruhr sector of Maastricht UAC shall route KONAN-KOK-REMBA-LNO.
4, 5. REMBA is required as intermediate waypoint during MIL activity. Eastbound traffic via Olno sector of Maastricht UAC shall file via REMBA and flights via Luxembourg sector of Maastricht UAC shall file the segment REMBA-RITAX. This applies to flights operating in the same flight level range as activated for EBTRASBZ (e.g. EBTRASBZ is active between FL195-FL365. A FL350 flight has to file KOK-REMBA or KOK-REMBA-RITAX. A FL370 flight does not need to follow this rule). The reference locations for the time and flight level check are the sectors EDYYBOLN/EDYYBLUX.
6, 7. KONAN as exit only available during the night and for EGKK arrivals.

Operational Goal:
1a. Traffic orientation. Flights to destination EHAM shall not plan via NORKU if coming from the South via the Ruhr sector nor if coming from the North/Northeast via the Jever/Holstein sector of Maastricht UAC. Flights via NORKU shall generally come from the East/Southeast.

For ARR EHAM there is not sufficient distance to descend on the short distance between the southern boundary of the military area and NORKU. During military activity, these flights shall plan a lateral re-routing to reach NORKU.
1c. ATC flight data processing system requirement. Traffic crossing the MAPOX Gate shall file via MAPOX or BIGGE before NORKU. This ensures automatic flight plan processing. DCT segments within MUAC FRA are possible (e.g. MAPOX DCT NORKU) as well as cross-border FRA options (e.g. MASEK DCT BIGGE).

Operational Goal:
When military training activities inside EBTRASBZ are conducted below FL365, traffic from / to nearby aerodromes shall not plan to overfly this military area above FL365 because the climb / descent profiles are usually not able to achieve the difference between FL365 and aerodrome altitude on the short distance between the military area and the location of the respective aerodrome. 
1, 2. Specified flights shall plan to laterally avoid EBTRASBZ at any flight level.
3. Specified flights are allowed to plan above EBTRASBZ if the profile is crossing the boundary between France/Brussels UIR already above FL365.
4. Specified flights are allowed to plan above EBTRASBZ if the profile is crossing the boundary between Maastricht UAC Delta/Brussels sectors already above FL365.
5, 6. Specified flights are allowed to plan above EBTRASBZ if the profile is crossing the boundary between Maastricht UAC Koksy/Nicky sectors already above FL365 during winter or above FL385 during summer season.
